<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Juncus</i> <i>oxymeris</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>xiphioides</i> or another iris-leaved rush is dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Carex</i> <i>serratodens</i>, <i>Cirsium</i> <i>fontinale</i> var. <i>campylon</i>, <i>Eleocharis</i> <i>macrostachya</i>, <i>Equisetum</i> <i>arvense</i>, <i>Hordeum</i> <i>brachyantherum</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>arcticus</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>effusus</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>patens</i>, <i>Lolium</i> <i>perenne</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>purshianus</i>, <i>Lythrum</i> <i>hyssopifolia</i>, <i>Mimulus</i> <i>guttatus</i>, <i>Polypogon</i> <i>monspeliensis</i>, <i>Rumex</i> <i>acetosella</i>, <i>Rumex</i> <i>crispus</i>, <i>Sisyrinchium</i> <i>bellum</i>, <i>Veronica</i> <i>americana</i> and <i>Vulpia</i> spp. Emergent shrubs may be present at low cover, including <i>Frangula</i> <i>californica</i> or <i>Rubus</i> spp. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Seeps, mainly on metamorphic, serpentine, and volcanic substrates. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Juncus oxymeris</i> as FACW and <i>Juncus xiphioides</i> as an OBL plant. </div>
</div>

		
